<TITLE> Vietnam to sell 1 lakh tonnes of rice to Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 6 (bdnews24.com) - Vietnam will export 100,000 tonnes of rice to Bangladesh by March, the foreign affairs adviser said Sunday. Bangladesh will initially get 20,000 tonnes of rice from the world's second largest rice exporting country, adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury said. The rest quantity is expected to reach by March, he said, adding that the Southeast Asian nation has responded positively to a recent request for the export. "Vietnam is willing to sell rice to us," Chowdhury told reporters in the ministry. Despite facing severe floods recently, Vietnam agreed to export rice, as it counts Bangladesh as a friend, he said. The latest development came after the adviser met the Vietnamese envoy to Dhaka on Jan 2 and requested him for the export. Bd
